pca-2head-update job info

Overview
- This sets up an automated cron job to run the bash script `pca-2head-update.sh` on a fixed schedule.
- The job runs under the root user, from the repo root directory `/root/rl-trader`.
- All stdout/stderr are appended to a log file so you can audit or troubleshoot runs.
 - The wrapper script sources `~/.bashrc` (with a PS1 override) so exported env vars like `OANDA_DEMO_ACCOUNT_ID` and `OANDA_DEMO_KEY` are available under cron. It also supports an optional `/root/rl-trader/.secrets/oanda.env` file.

Schedule
- Runs every Sunday through Thursday at 6:24 PM America/New_York (US Eastern).
- The cron uses `CRON_TZ=America/New_York`, so Daylight Saving Time is handled automatically.

Relevant files and paths
- Script: /root/rl-trader/pca-2head-update.sh
- Working directory: /root/rl-trader
- Log file: /root/rl-trader/logs/pca-2head-update.log

