Troubleshooting
- Ensure the script is executable:
```
chmod +x /root/rl-trader/pca-2head-update.sh
```
- Check if cron is triggering the job (Ubuntu/Debian):
```
grep CRON /var/log/syslog | tail -n 50
journalctl -u cron -n 100 --no-pager
```
- If the script relies on environment variables or virtualenvs, source them inside the script or wrap the command in the cron entry.
 - This wrapper already sources `~/.bashrc` and will pick up exported environment variables even under cron. It also resolves the Python interpreter (prefers `/root/aid-env/bin/python3`), so `python: command not found` errors are avoided.
- The log file can grow over time. Consider configuring log rotation (e.g., via logrotate) if needed.

Notes
- The job runs with a minimal environment. We explicitly set `PATH` in the crontab entry. If the script needs additional environment setup, add it in the script or define variables above the cron line.
- Because `CRON_TZ` is set, the schedule is always interpreted in Eastern Time and adjusts for DST automatically.
